<b><font size=+1>
List:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2">namedroppers</a>
Subject:    Changes at the root servers
From:       <a href="?a=95837784200005&r=1&w=2">Paul Mockapetris &lt;pvm () venera ! isi ! edu&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198711">1987-11-12 17:08:36</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926994&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926994&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Effective immediately, the root server on A.ISI.EDU will begin
distributing SOA RRs in the authority section for the purpose of
allowing negative caching as described in the new domain RFCs.  (The new
RFCs have been available in draft form for some time, and should hit the
street real soon as real RFCs.)  Assuming that this does not cause severe
problems, the new server code will be distributed to other TOPS-20 root
servers in the near future.  Please inform me of any problems.

Measurements on the root servers have shown that they are processing a
bogon flux approximately equal to the useful packet rate, with bursts
exceeding the useful packet rate.  The suggestion has been made that the
root servers discard a real packet from host X for every bogon received
from X.

The death watch continues for the root server on C.ISI.EDU.  A one week
reprieve has postponed the burial at C from tomorrow to next week.
Presumably Jason was unavailable.

paul

